RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 53. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BEAUTY IN MOTION raced in the three path around the first turn, chased the leader up the backstretch, began a bid from the two path coming around the second bend and held clear in the lane. EXAGERADORA raced in the three path early, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the three and four path, launched a bid entering the stretch and gained ground late. PEACE PACT raced in the middle of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, came around the second turn in the two path and improved position in the stretch. DUSTED raced in the two path around the first turn, settled in the middle of the pack on the inside for the run up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the three path and improved position from there. RED RIVER SUSI saved ground around the first turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the rail around the second turn and weakened in the final furlong. PAUL'S TRICKY TALE dueled on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, dropped back while saving ground around the far turn and continued to fade from there. MS KAYS COWGIRL raced in the two path early, trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and made no bid. DON'T ANNOY ME raced in the four path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far turn from the two path and was empty from there.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 2 6F Dirt CR: 55. Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 12, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROVIDING chased the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, began a bid while saving ground around the bend, drew off in the lane and was vanned off after the wire. WIN OR CELLAR tracked the pace setters on the outside through the opening quarter of a mile, moved up while racing in the two path around the turn and could not go with the winner in the stretch but chased that rival home from there. THROWBACK pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, bumping with ANGELIC GAL when G G'S DARK STAR drifted out, navigated the bend from the three and four path and was outkicked in the lane. G G'S DARK STAR dueled on the inside up the backstretch, drifted out bumping with ANGELIC GAL and THROWBACK in the process, raced in the three path around the turn and gave way entering the stretch. ANGELIC GAL dueled between horses early, bumping with both THROWBACK and G G'S DARK STAR when her inside rival drifted out, came around the turn in the three and four path and tired in the lane. A STEWARDS INQUIRY WAS MADE INTO THE BACKSTRETCH. UPON REVIEW, HORSE 1, G G'S DARK STAR WAS DISQUALIFIED AND PLACED LAST FOR INTERFERENCE.

TURBO MILLIE saved ground early, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far bend in the two path and kept on in the lane, no match for the winner. EASTERN SUNRISE dueled on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, chased the frontrunner from the two path around the second turn and weakened in the lane. AMORICA bobbled slightly leaving the gate, raced in the two path around the first bend, settled off the pace on the outside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in the three and four path and showed no kick. FOREVER HOPEFUL stalked the leaders on the outside through the opening half mile, dropped back while racing in the two and three path around the far turn and continued to flatten out from there. INTOLERANT saved ground around the first turn, continued up the backstretch and around the second bend off the pace on the inside and made no bid.

WINE IN THE DARK bumped mildly with the horse to her outside at the break, chased the leader from the two path through the opening half mile, came around the far turn still in the two path and kept on to the wire. BOUNTY KILLAH raced in the two path around the first bend, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle while saving ground around the far turn and weakened in the final furlong. APPLE LOVER raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening half mile, swung out to the three and four path coming around the second bend and passed tiring horses in the lane. BIG SIS NIC raced in the middle of the pack on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the three path and finished evenly. APRIL'S GOLD raced off the pace on the outside around the first turn and up the backstretch, saved ground around the second bend and was empty in the lane. AKIVA raced in the two path around the first turn, settled at the back of the pack between horses for the run up the backstretch, trailed the field from the two path around the far turn and was not a factor.
